The paper deals with decomposition and characterization of digraphs, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and graph theory (cs.GT). The concepts of strong digraphs and spanning subdigraphs are also relevant to algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also involves the study of products and compositions of digraphs, which can be classified under numerical analysis (cs.NA) and scientific computing (cs.SI).
